# Customer Churn Analysis â€“ End-to-End Data Analytics Case Study

## ğŸ“Œ Business Problem
Customer churn is a critical issue for subscription-based businesses, directly impacting revenue and long-term growth. This project analyzes customer behavior data to identify the key drivers of churn and provide actionable, data-driven recommendations to improve customer retention.

---

## ğŸ“Š Dataset
- **Source:** IBM Telco Customer Churn Dataset
- **Rows:** ~7,000 customers
- **Target Variable:** Churn (Yes/No)
- **Key Features:**
  - Contract type
  - Customer tenure
  - Monthly charges
  - Payment method
  - Service subscriptions

---

## ğŸ› ï¸ Approach
1. Loaded and inspected raw customer data
2. Cleaned and prepared data for analysis
3. Performed exploratory data analysis (EDA)
4. Visualized churn patterns across customer segments
5. Identified key churn drivers
6. Delivered business-focused insights and recommendations

---

## ğŸ” Key Insights
- Customers on **month-to-month contracts** churn significantly more than long-term customers
- **Low-tenure customers** are at the highest risk of churn
- Higher **monthly charges** are strongly associated with churn
- Customers using **manual payment methods (electronic check)** churn more frequently than auto-pay users

---

## ğŸ’¡ Business Recommendations
- Encourage customers to switch from month-to-month to long-term contracts through incentives
- Improve onboarding and engagement during the first year of customer tenure
- Offer targeted discounts or bundled plans for high-cost customers
- Promote auto-payment methods to reduce churn friction

